{
  "texts": [
    "The inception of AI can be traced back to Alan Turing's seminal 1950 paper, \"Computing Machinery and Intelligence\" (Turing, 1950).",
    "In this work, Turing posed the pivotal question: \"Can machines think?\"",
    "and introduced the Turing Test as a benchmark for assessing machine intelligence.",
    "The Turing Test establishes a rigorous standard for AI advancement, aiming for machines capable of replicating human-like dialogue and logical thinking to the extent that they are indistinguishable from humans.",
    "In the 1950s, the field of artificial intelligence began to take shape."
  ]
}